To Make the Mousse: Place all the ingredients in a food processor and blend for 1 to 2 minutes until smooth, with the consistency of a thick pudding. Add more avocado if too thin, Scrape down the sides of the container with a spatula as needed. Vanilla Cream: Place the cashews, coconut oil, water, agave nectar, and vanilla into a high-power blender and process until very smooth. Chill the mousse and cream for 2 hours or until firm, then layer into parfait glasses using a pastry bag or a spoon. Stored separately, the mousse will keep for 3 days in the refrigerator and the cream will keep for 1 week.